These can be simplified like:




        Suggested change











                try {



                  accumuloClient.tableOperations().create(tableName);



                  fail("IllegalArgumentException was not thrown");



                } catch (IllegalArgumentException exc) {



                  assertTrue(!accumuloClient.tableOperations().exists(tableName));



                }



                assertThrows(IllegalArgumentException.class, () -> accumuloClient.tableOperations().create(tableName));



                assertFalse(accumuloClient.tableOperations().exists(tableName));






The Assert.assertThrows also returns the exception, so you can do additional checks to check the exception's getMessage() and, if you wish, the getCause().
You can also create the name using commons-lang3's String tableName = StringUtils.repeat('a', MAX_TABLE_NAME_LEN);
You can also verify the length of the string in an assert statement. Additional checks would include max length plus and minus one.
These comments also apply to the namespace checks.

